DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.



loadMacros("PG.pl", "PGbasicmacros.pl", "PGchoicemacros.pl",

"PGanswermacros.pl",

"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl");



install_problem_grader(~~&std_problem_grader);
TEXT(beginproblem());

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;





# output the text of the problem



$a = random(2,10,1);

$b = random(2,10,1);

$c = random(2,10,1);



TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));



Consider the inequality : \( | $b - $a x | < $c \)



The solution of this inequality consists of one or more of the
intervals \( (-\infty, A) \), \( (A,B) \) and \( (B,\infty) \) where 
\( A < B \).

$PAR

Find \( A \) \{ ans_rule(10) \}

$PAR

Find \( B \) \{ ans_rule(10) \}

$PAR

For each interval, answer YES or NO to whether the interval is included in 
the solution.

$PAR

\( (-\infty, A) \) \{ ans_rule(10) \}

$PAR

\( (A,B) \) \{ ans_rule(10) \}

$PAR

\( (B,\infty) \) \{ ans_rule(10) \}

EOT





$ans1 = (-$c+$b)/$a; 

$ans2 = ($c+$b)/$a; 

$ans3 = "no";

$ans4 = "yes";

$ans5 = "no";



ANS(num_cmp($ans1));

ANS(num_cmp($ans2));

ANS(str_cmp($ans3));

ANS(str_cmp($ans4));

ANS(str_cmp($ans5));



